  "prompt": "Does Google take into account that you are speeding while calculating your ETA?",
  "response": "Google Maps does not take into account whether you are speeding or not when calculating your estimated time of arrival (ETA). It uses historical traffic data, real-time traffic conditions, and the speed limit of the roads to estimate the time it will take to reach your destination. \n\nHowever, if you are driving faster than the speed limit, your ETA might be sooner than what Google Maps predicts. Conversely, if you are driving slower, your ETA might be later. But Google Maps itself does not adjust its ETA based on your actual speed. It's always a good idea to obey traffic laws and drive safely, even if it means arriving at your destination a bit later than you'd like.",
